# AP Spring Mini Project

A C++ object-oriented university project for Ferdowsi University, inspired by online restaurant service platforms such as SnappFood.

***

## Overview

This project is developed as part of the **AP-SPRING** course at **Ferdowsi University** under the supervision of **Professor Javad Sobouti**.

The main idea is to design and implement a **restaurant service system** similar to SnappFood using **C++** and **Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)** principles.

***

## Project Goals

- Practice Object-Oriented Programming in C++
- Design a clean and understandable software architecture
- Apply core OOP concepts:
  - Encapsulation
  - Inheritance
  - Polymorphism
  - Abstraction
  - Modularity
- Learn version control with Git and GitHub
- Integrate a persistent database (SQLite)

***

## Technologies and Tools

| Tool / Technology    | Details                    |
|----------------------|----------------------------|
| Language             | C++ (C++17)                |
| Paradigm             | Object-Oriented Programming |
| Editor               | Visual Studio Code         |
| Compiler             | GCC / g++                  |
| Version Control      | Git                        |
| Repository Platform  | GitHub                     |
| Database             | SQLite (via sqlite3)       |

***

## Project Concept

This project simulates an online food and restaurant service platform.  
It is designed to manage users, restaurants, menus, and ordering operations in an object-oriented way.

### Key Features

- **User Roles:**
  - `Admin` вЂ” manages restaurants and users, assigns managers
  - `RestaurantManager` вЂ” manages the menu and items of their assigned restaurant
  - `Customer` вЂ” browses restaurants, views menus, and places orders

- **Item System:**
  - Base class `Item` with price validation, tax calculation, and `FinalPrice()` support
  - Derived class `Food` with calories, vegan flag, and preparation time
  - `ItemType` enum for polymorphic type identification

- **Restaurant Management:**
  - Full CRUD operations via `RestaurantDAO` using SQLite
  - Active/inactive status filtering
  - Manager-to-restaurant assignment system

- **Database Layer:**
  - DAO (Data Access Object) pattern for `Restaurant`, `User`, and `Item` entities
  - Persistent storage using SQLite embedded database (`food_app.db`)
  - Parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection

***

